<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>

<p>Upper part of the shaft of a <rs type="material" key="marmor">blue-white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">column</rs> (diam. across the top <measure dim="diameter" type="length">0.42</measure>).</p></div><div type="description" n="text"><head>Description of Text</head><p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> in an area which is worn or broken away.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Capitals with restrained seriphs; <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.025</measure></p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>

<p>
<date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0200" exact="none">Second century A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">monument</rs>, <rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p></div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Διογένης">Διο<supplied reason="lost">γ</supplied><unclear reason="damage">έν</unclear>ης</name><lb n="2"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Λέων">Λέο<unclear reason="damage">ντ</unclear>ος</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w><lb n="3"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἱέρων">Ἱέρωνος</name>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w><lb n="4"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Διογένης">Δ<unclear reason="damage">ι</unclear>ογένους</name></persName></persName></persName></persName>  <w lemma="ὁ">τοὺς</w><lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost"><space extent="6" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/></supplied>  <w lemma="ἕξ"><supplied reason="lost">ἕ</supplied>ξ</w>  <space extent="6" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/><lb n="6"/><w lemma="κίων"><supplied reason="lost">κεί</supplied>ονας</w>  <w lemma="σύν">σὺν</w><lb n="7"/><w lemma="σπεῖρα"><unclear reason="damage">σ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">πε</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ί</unclear>ραις</w>  <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w><lb n="8"/><w lemma="κεφαλή">κεφαλεῖσιν</w><lb n="9"/> <w lemma="ἐκ">ἐκ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶν</w> <w lemma="ἑαυτός">ἑαυτοῦ</w><lb n="10"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">Δήμῳ</w></ab>
</div>


<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Diogenes son of Leon the son of Hieron the son of Diogenes (gave) the six columns with ?tori and capitals from his own money for the People</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>For other column dedications from the Hadrianic Baths see two from a group of fourteen dedicated by Nestor and Zenon (<xref type="inscription" n="1111" href="050205">5.205</xref> [=Mendel 173], and four from the six dedicated by Artemon (<xref type="inscription" n="1110" href="050002">5.2</xref> [=Mendel 172]) and (a fragment) <xref type="iAph">1113</xref> [=Boulanger B Page 23, no 29].</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>
Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown, but very probably from <rs type="monuList" cert="low">Hadrianic Baths</rs>.</rs>
Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">South Agora</rs>: Portico of Tiberius SW; the southern end of the west portico.</rs>
; Last known location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum</rs>
</p>
</div>
